Satiation pilots

2023-11-12

Introduction

We predict that conditions that are more representable (lower entropy of meaning) are more satiable, and conditions that have a clear alternative (lower entropy of form) are less satiable. So satiation should occur most readily in conditions with low Hm, high Hf.

We measure Hf by calculating the entropy over our form codes. We measure Hm in two ways: first by also calculating the entropy over meaning codes, and second by participants’ ratings for how confident they were that they understood the sentence.

Satiation effect

First, we look at the satiation effect, both within and across participants. For each participant, we plot block number against acceptability rating, grouped by condition. Each data point represents the acceptability rating of one item. We then plot a single graph where each data point is an average of all the ratings for that condition on that block.

Satiation vs individual entropies
